HEADWORD: Discourtesy
<hw>Dis*cour"te*sy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>dis-</ets> + <ets>courtesy</ets>: cf. OF.
<ets>descourtoisie</ets>.]</ety> <def>Rudeness of behavior or language;
ill manners; manifestation of disrespect; incivility.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Be calm in arguing; for fierceness makes⟦br⟧
Error a fault, and truth <qex>discourtesy</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Herbert.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Discourtship</ent>⟦br⟧
